{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "b7a1e2c0-5f3a-4a2b-9c11-smartbanking02",
    "name": "Smart Banking & Wallet System",
    "description": "End-to-end collection for all services (auth, user, account, wallet, transaction) plus the gateway.\n\nRun the folders top-to-bottom (or use the Collection Runner): Auth -> User -> Account -> Wallet -> Transaction -> Gateway.\n\nHOW IT WORKS\n- The 'Auth > Register' request generates a UNIQUE username/email per run (a pre-request script), so every full run creates a brand-new customer whose profile is auto-created in the User Service. This avoids stale-user failures (a customer that has no profile is rejected by account/wallet with 404/503).\n- Register captures customerId; Login captures accessToken/refreshToken/customerId; create requests capture accountId/walletId/transactionId into collection variables.\n- Business folders hit each service DIRECTLY with an X-Customer-Id header (works without the gateway). The 'Gateway' folder proves JWT routing + identity-header injection through :8080.\n\nPREREQS: config-server, eureka and all services must be UP (./run-all.sh). MongoDB on :27017. Build/run with JDK 21.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "gatewayUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8080" },
    { "key": "authUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8081" },
    { "key": "userUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8082" },
    { "key": "accountUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8083" },
    { "key": "walletUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8084" },
    { "key": "txnUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8085" },
    { "key": "configUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8888" },
    { "key": "eurekaUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8761" },
    { "key": "username", "value": "alice" },
    { "key": "email", "value": "alice@example.com" },
    { "key": "phone", "value": "9990001111" },
    { "key": "password", "value": "secret123" },
    { "key": "internalUserApiKey", "value": "change-me-internal-user-service-key" },
    { "key": "accessToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "refreshToken", "value": "" },
    { "key": "customerId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "internalUserId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "internalEmail", "value": "" },
    { "key": "internalPhone", "value": "" },
    { "key": "accountId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "accountId2", "value": "" },
    { "key": "walletId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "walletId2", "value": "" },
    { "key": "transactionId", "value": "" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "00 - Auth (:8081)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register",
          "event": [
            { "listen": "prerequest", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": [
              "// Fresh user per run so the profile is created cleanly and downstream steps pass.",
              "// email + phone are unique-constrained in the User Service, so make them unique per run.",
              "const ts = Date.now();",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('username', 'alice_' + ts);",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('email', 'alice_' + ts + '@example.com');",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('phone', String(ts).slice(-10));"
            ] } },
            { "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": [
              "pm.test('registered (201) or duplicate (409)', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([201, 409]));",
              "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
              "  const j = pm.response.json();",
              "  pm.test('returns customerId', () => pm.expect(j.customerId).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
              "  pm.collectionVariables.set('customerId', j.customerId);",
              "}"
            ] } }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [ { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" } ],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"username\":\"{{username}}\",\"email\":\"{{email}}\",\"password\":\"{{password}}\",\"fullName\":\"Alice Anderson\",\"phoneNumber\":\"{{phone}}\",\"address\":{\"line1\":\"12 MG Road\",\"city\":\"Bengaluru\",\"state\":\"KA\",\"pincode\":\"560001\"}}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } },
            "url": { "raw": "{{authUrl}}/auth/register", "host": [ "{{authUrl}}" ], "path": [ "auth", "register" ] },
            "description": "Creates credentials AND (service-to-service) the customer profile in the User Service, using the generated customerId as the profile id."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            { "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": [
              "pm.test('login 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const j = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('returns access token', () => pm.expect(j.token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', j.token);",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('refreshToken', j.refreshToken);",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('customerId', j.customerId);",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('username', j.username);"
            ] } }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [ { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" } ],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"usernameOrEmail\":\"{{username}}\",\"password\":\"{{password}}\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } },
            "url": { "raw": "{{authUrl}}/auth/login", "host": [ "{{authUrl}}" ], "path": [ "auth", "login" ] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Refresh token",
          "event": [
            { "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": [
              "pm.test('refresh 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const j = pm.response.json();",
              "if (j.token) pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', j.token);"
            ] } }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [ { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" } ],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"refreshToken\":\"{{refreshToken}}\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } },
            "url": { "raw": "{{authUrl}}/auth/refresh", "host": [ "{{authUrl}}" ], "path": [ "auth", "refresh" ] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Validate token",
          "event": [
            { "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": [
              "pm.test('valid token 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "pm.test('valid=true', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().valid).to.eql(true));"
            ] } }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [ { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" } ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{authUrl}}/auth/validate", "host": [ "{{authUrl}}" ], "path": [ "auth", "validate" ] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get current user (/me)",
          "event": [
            { "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": [
              "pm.test('me 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
            ] } }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [ { "key": "X-Auth-Username", "value": "{{username}}" } ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{authUrl}}/auth/me", "host": [ "{{authUrl}}" ], "path": [ "auth", "me" ] },
            "description": "Behind the gateway the X-Auth-Username header is injected from the JWT; here we send it by hand to hit the service directly."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get all users (admin)",
          "event": [
            { "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": [
              "pm.test('admin list 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
            ] } }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [ { "key": "X-Auth-Roles", "value": "ADMIN" } ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{authUrl}}/auth/users", "host": [ "{{authUrl}}" ], "path": [ "auth", "users" ] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout",
          "event": [
            { "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": [
              "pm.test('logout 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
            ] } }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [ { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" } ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{authUrl}}/auth/logout", "host": [ "{{authUrl}}" ], "path": [ "auth", "logout" ] }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "01 - User (:8082)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get my profile (created at registration)",
          "event": [
            { "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": [
              "pm.test('profile 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "pm.test('id == customerId', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().id).to.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get('customerId')));"
            ] } }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [ { "key": "X-Customer-Id", "value": "{{customerId}}" } ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{userUrl}}/users/{{customerId}}", "host": [ "{{userUrl}}" ], "path": [ "users", "{{customerId}}" ] },
            "description": "Registration auto-creates the profile with _id == customerId. Ownership check requires X-Customer-Id == path id."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update my profile",
          "event": [
            { "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": [
              "pm.test('update 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
            ] } }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Customer-Id", "value": "{{customerId}}" }
            ],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"fullName\":\"Alice A. Anderson\",\"email\":\"{{email}}\",\"phoneNumber\":\"{{phone}}\",\"address\":{\"line1\":\"99 Brigade Road\",\"city\":\"Bengaluru\",\"state\":\"KA\",\"pincode\":\"560025\"}}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } },
            "url": { "raw": "{{userUrl}}/users/{{customerId}}", "host": [ "{{userUrl}}" ], "path": [ "users", "{{customerId}}" ] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create user (internal, API key)",
          "event": [
            { "listen": "prerequest", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": [
              "// Internal endpoint requires the caller to supply the profile id. Use fresh id/email/phone so this demo never collides (User Service enforces unique email + phone).",
              "const ts = Date.now();",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('internalUserId', 'cust-' + ts);",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('internalEmail', 'internal.demo.' + ts + '@example.com');",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('internalPhone', String(ts).slice(-10));"
            ] } },
            { "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": [
              "pm.test('201 created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
              "const j = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('echoes id', () => pm.expect(j.id).to.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get('internalUserId')));"
            ] } }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Internal-Api-Key", "value": "{{internalUserApiKey}}" }
            ],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"id\":\"{{internalUserId}}\",\"fullName\":\"Internal Demo\",\"email\":\"{{internalEmail}}\",\"phoneNumber\":\"{{internalPhone}}\",\"address\":{\"line1\":\"12 MG Road\",\"city\":\"Bengaluru\",\"state\":\"KA\",\"pincode\":\"560001\"}}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } },
            "url": { "raw": "{{userUrl}}/users/internal", "host": [ "{{userUrl}}" ], "path": [ "users", "internal" ] },
            "description": "Service-to-service endpoint the Auth Service uses during registration. Requires the X-Internal-Api-Key header and the profile 'id' (the customerId). Not exposed through the gateway."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete user (internal, compensating)",
          "event": [
            { "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": [
              "pm.test('204 no content', () => pm.response.to.have.status(204));"
            ] } }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [ { "key": "X-Internal-Api-Key", "value": "{{internalUserApiKey}}" } ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{userUrl}}/users/internal/{{internalUserId}}", "host": [ "{{userUrl}}" ], "path": [ "users", "internal", "{{internalUserId}}" ] },
            "description": "Idempotent compensating delete. Auth calls this to remove an orphan profile if the credential write fails after profile creation. Cleans up the demo profile created above."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
